[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.HtmlParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:40[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: 3c99eeb1380e104c[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reports an OS Command Injection vulnerability [0m[1;39m([0m[39mclassified as [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFuzzerSecurityIssueCritical[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m detected during fuzzing of the Apache Tika HTML [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser. The vulnerability occurs in the `ExternalParser` class when executing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal commands with potentially attacker-controlled data. A patch was applied [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat added file path validation and modified the command execution mechanism, but [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe fuzzer still reports the same OS Command Injection vulnerability after the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch. The vulnerability persists at line [0m[1;36m386[0m[39m of ExternalParser.java [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpreviously at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m314[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating that while the patch made structural changes, it did not [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuccessfully prevent the command injection vulnerability from being triggered.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reveals an OS Command Injection security vulnerability detected [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby Jazzer's sanitizer during fuzzing operations. The stack trace shows:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The vulnerability is triggered at `OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich is Jazzer's hook for detecting OS command injection attempts[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The execution flow originates from `[0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m314[0m[39m in [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mExternalParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The call chain traces back through multiple parsers: ExternalParser → [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mParserDecorator → CompositeParser → AutoDetectParser → DelegatingParser → [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mParsingEmbeddedDocumentExtractor[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The trigger point is in the HTML parsing flow: [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mHtmlHandler.handleDataURIScheme[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mHtmlHandler.startElement[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → JSoupParser[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. The fuzzer entry point is `[0m[1;35mHtmlParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which calls [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mparseOne[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to process fuzzer-generated input[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue indicates that attacker-controlled data can reach the OS command [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution point, potentially allowing remote code execution. The DEDUP_TOKEN [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m3c99eeb1380e104c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is provided to track duplicate findings of this issue.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch implements several security measures in the `ExternalParser` class:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **New Validation Method**: Added a `[0m[1;35mvalidateFilePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method that:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Checks for null or empty paths[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Requires absolute paths to prevent directory traversal[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rejects control characters [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing `[0m[1;35mCharacter.isISOControl[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rejects shell metacharacters: `;`, `|`, `&`, `$`, `` ` ``, `[0m[1;39m([0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `<`, `>`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`*`, `?`, `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`, `'`, `"`[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Enforces a maximum path length of [0m[1;36m4096[0m[39m characters[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Provides detailed error messages indicating the specific character and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mposition that failed validation[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Command Building Modifications**: Changed the command array construction:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When a single command string is provided, it is no longer split by spaces[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Instead, the single command is placed as-is in a single-element array[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This prevents breaking command structure with special characters in paths[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Token Replacement with Validation**:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before replacing `IN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m_FILE_TOKEN`, the input file path is validated using [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mvalidateFilePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before replacing `OUT[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m_FILE_TOKEN`, the output file path is validated using [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mvalidateFilePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validation occurs before the tokens are substituted into the command array[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Process Execution Changes**:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replaced `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls with `ProcessBuilder`[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The ProcessBuilder approach is documented as more secure since it does not [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoke a shell by default[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removed the conditional logic that chose between `[0m[1;35mexec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mexec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` variants[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added explicit exception handling with a TikaException throw[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the fuzzer still detects the same OS Command Injection [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability with the following observations:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Same Vulnerability Type**: The exception type remains [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command Injection`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Same Detection Point**: Still caught at [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mOsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Updated Line Number**: The vulnerability now occurs at line [0m[1;36m386[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpreviously [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m314[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, reflecting the code additions in the patch[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Same Execution Path**: The [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is now at the trigger point [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstead of [0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Different DEDUP_TOKEN**: Changed from `3c99eeb1380e104c` to [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cc6f61fd5cfb05e7`, indicating a different [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbut related[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m instance of the [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Identical Call Stack Structure**: The overall call chain remains the same, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginating from HTML parsing with data URI schemes[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fact that ProcessBuilder is now in the stack trace [0m[1;39m([0m[39minstead of Runtime.exec[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirms that the patch was applied, but the command injection vulnerability is [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill being detected by the fuzzer's sanitizer.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo understand why the patch was ineffective and obtain a complete picture of the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability, the following areas should be investigated:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Command Configuration Source**: Examine where and how the `command` array is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpopulated in ExternalParser, particularly:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How external parser configurations are loaded[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether the command template itself could contain malicious content[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The full lifecycle of command definition from configuration to execution[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Data URI Handling**: Since the trigger originates from [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mHtmlHandler.handleDataURIScheme[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, investigate:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How data URIs are parsed and processed[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - What content types trigger external parser invocation[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether malicious data can be embedded in data URI schemes that bypass [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Validation Bypass Scenarios**: Determine if the file path validation can be [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbypassed:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Paths that are absolute but still contain exploitable elements[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether the command array elements beyond the file paths are validated[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If special encoding or character representations can bypass the character [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Command Array Elements**: Analyze all elements of the command array:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The base command [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and its origin[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any arguments that don't go through validation[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether command-line switches or flags could be injected[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **ProcessBuilder Configuration**: Examine if additional ProcessBuilder security [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msettings are needed:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Environment variable handling[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Working directory configuration[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Redirection settings that might be exploitable[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Parser Configuration Chain**: Trace how ExternalParser instances are [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfigured:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The CompositeParser configuration[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AutoDetectParser's external parser selection logic[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any dynamic parser registration mechanisms[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Temporary File Creation**: Investigate the `[0m[1;35mtmp.createTemporaryFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmechanism:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether temporary file names can be influenced by attacker input[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - File creation location and permissions[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential race conditions in temporary file handling[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe persistence of the vulnerability suggests that either the validation is being [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbypassed, the command structure itself is compromised before the validation point, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor there are additional injection vectors beyond file paths that are not addressed [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby the patch.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Any other error during validation[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Error validating exiftool path, rejecting: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, path, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Continue with existing method logic below[0m[33m...[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ExternalParser exifToolParser = [0m[1;35mgetExistingExifToolParser[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m rest of the existing method[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m: Retain Previous Patch Changes to ExternalParser.java[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKeep all changes from the previous patch to `ExternalParser.java`:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Keep the [0m[1;35mvalidateFilePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m280[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m345[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - provides defense in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth for file path tokens[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Keep the ProcessBuilder usage** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline ~[0m[1;36m386[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - more secure than [0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Keep the command array handling** that doesn't split by spaces - prevents [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcommand structure manipulation[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThese changes provide additional security layers even though they don't fix the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot cause.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m: Update [0m[1;35mresetExifTool[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to Remove Metadata Cleanup[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn the `[0m[1;35mresetExifTool[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m438[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, keep the line that removes the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata entry:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mmetadata.remove[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"exiftool_path"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis ensures the document metadata value is cleaned up, though it's no longer used [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor command configuration.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Complete Fix Summary[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Files to Patch:**[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **tika-parsers/[0m[33m...[0m[35m/tika-parser-html-module/.../[0m[95mHtmlHandler.java[0m[39m:**[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add imports: `java.nio.file.Files`, `java.nio.file.Path`, [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`java.nio.file.Paths`[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add logger if missing: `private static final Logger LOG = [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mLoggerFactory.getLogger[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlHandler.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace lines [0m[1;36m363[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m364[0m[39m: Change from `[0m[1;35mmetadata.get[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"html_meta:exiftool_path"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto `[0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"tika.exiftool.path"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add validation at start of `[0m[1;35mconfigureExifTool[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`: Comprehensive path [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation before use[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **tika-core/[0m[33m...[0m[35m/external/[0m[95mExternalParser.java[0m[39m:**[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Retain all previous patch changes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvalidateFilePath, ProcessBuilder, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These provide defense in depth[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Justification for Updated Strategy[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why this completely fixes the vulnerability:**[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Source Control**: Document metadata can no longer configure commands [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m363[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **System Property Only**: Only trusted system properties can configure exiftool [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Multi-Layer Validation**: Even system properties are validated [0m[1;39m([0m[39mabsolute path,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexists, executable, correct filename[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth**: Previous ProcessBuilder changes still provide additional [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **No Shell Invocation**: ProcessBuilder avoids shell metacharacter exploitation[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How it preserves existing functionality:**[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **HTML Parsing**: All HTML parsing continues normally[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Data URI Handling**: Data URI schemes are still processed[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Exiftool Support**: Users can still configure exiftool via system property[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Embedded Documents**: Embedded document extraction still works[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Metadata Extraction**: Normal metadata extraction is unaffected[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why previous patch failed and this one succeeds:**[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Previous patch**: Validated file path tokens [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m/OUT[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but command itself[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas attacker-controlled[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **This patch**: Prevents attacker control of the command by removing document [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata as configuration source[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Root cause addressed**: The fundamental issue [0m[1;39m([0m[39muntrusted source → command [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfig[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is fixed[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Defense in depth**: Previous patch changes are retained for additional [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Edge cases handled:**[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **No system property set**: Code gracefully handles null/empty [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline check after[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Invalid paths**: Validation returns error code [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, preventing command execution[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Non-exiftool executables**: Filename check prevents arbitrary command [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Symlinks**: `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` resolves symlinks, then validates the target[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Relative paths**: Converted to absolute, preventing directory traversal[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Special characters**: Not an issue since command is now from trusted source[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Migration path for users:**[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUsers who need custom exiftool paths should:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```bash[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Set system property when running Tika[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava -Dtika.exiftool.[0m[33mpath[0m[39m=[0m[35m/usr/local/bin/[0m[95mexiftool[0m[39m -jar tika-app.jar [0m[33m...[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOr in code:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mSystem.setProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"tika.exiftool.path"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"/usr/local/bin/exiftool"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is the correct, secure approach for configuration - from trusted sources, not [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdocument content.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.CompositeParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCompositeParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:298[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.AutoDetectParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[39mAutoDetectParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:204[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mcom.example.HtmlParserFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:69[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.HtmlParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:40[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: 3c99eeb1380e104c[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue identifies an OS Command Injection vulnerability in Apache Tika's[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHTML parser module. A fuzzer detected that attacker-controlled data from HTML [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdocuments can be used to execute arbitrary OS commands through the ExternalParser [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmechanism. The patch attempt aimed to prevent this vulnerability by: [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m blocking [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdocument-controlled metadata from specifying the exiftool path in HtmlHandler, and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m adding input validation in ExternalParser to prevent command injection. [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, the patch resulted in a compilation failure due to a syntax error in the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHtmlHandler.java file - specifically a duplicate class declaration and an unclosed [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode block.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack trace reveals that:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The vulnerability originates in `[0m[1;35mExternalParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m314[0m[39m, where [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The execution path traces through the HTML parsing pipeline: AutoDetectParser → [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCompositeParser → HtmlParser → HtmlHandler[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The critical vulnerability point is in `[0m[1;35mHtmlHandler.handleDataURIScheme[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m377[0m[39m, which processes data URI schemes embedded in HTML[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The handler calls `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which eventually triggers external parser [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution with potentially malicious command strings[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer's security hook [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m detected [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe unsafe command execution[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue demonstrates that HTML documents with specially crafted data URIs can [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minject metadata that controls external command execution, particularly through the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"exiftool_path"[0m[39m metadata field.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Description[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies two key files:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. HtmlHandler.java modifications:**[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds imports for `java.nio.file` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFiles, Path, Paths[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and SLF4J Logger[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduces a duplicate class declaration on line [0m[1;36m61[0m[39m: `public class HtmlHandler [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextends TextContentHandler` while the original declaration `class HtmlHandler [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextends TextContentHandler` remains on line [0m[1;36m60[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds a static Logger instance[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modifies the `[0m[1;35mhandleDataURIScheme[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m368[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Ignore the `html_met[0m[1;92ma:e[0m[39mxiftool_path` metadata from documents with a warning log[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Instead read exiftool path only from system property `tika.exiftool.path`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Implements a new `[0m[1;35mconfigureExifTool[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method with extensive [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Rejects null/empty paths[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Resolves to absolute normalized paths[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Validates file existence, executability, and regular file type[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Checks that the filename contains [0m[32m"exiftool"[0m[39m string[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Catches SecurityException and other exceptions during validation[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Returns error code [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m for any validation failure[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. ExternalParser.java modifications:**[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds a new private method `[0m[1;35mvalidateFilePath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Checks for null/empty paths[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Requires absolute paths[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Scans each character for control characters [0m[1;39m([0m[39mISO control chars[0m[1;39m)[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Rejects shell metacharacters: `;`, `|`, `&`, `$`, `` ` ``, `[0m[1;39m([0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `<`, `>`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`*`, `?`, `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`, `'`, `"`[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Enforces maximum path length of [0m[1;36m4096[0m[39m characters[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modifies the `[0m[1;35mparse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m277[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Remove the command splitting logic that splits single commands by spaces[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Keeps command as a single element when command.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Calls `[0m[1;35mvalidateFilePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on both IN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m_FILE_TOKEN and OUT[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m_FILE_TOKEN [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplacements[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Switches from `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to `ProcessBuilder` for process [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Ensures TikaException is thrown on process start failure[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Compilation Error Details[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe build fails with error:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[39mERROR[0m[1;39m][0m[39m [0m[35m/src/project-parent/tika/.../[0m[95mHtmlHandler.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m646[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m][0m[39m reached end of file [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile parsing[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis error indicates:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. A syntax error at line [0m[1;36m646[0m[39m, column [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mend of file[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. An unclosed block structure [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmissing closing brace[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The duplicate class declaration on line [0m[1;36m61[0m[39m creates a malformed class structure[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The original `class HtmlHandler extends TextContentHandler` on line [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m is not [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremoved, causing the duplicate declaration[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo fully understand and address the command injection vulnerability, the following [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponents should be examined:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **ExternalParser command construction pipeline**: Review how command arrays are [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuilt and how tokens [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m_FILE_TOKEN, OUT[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[39m_FILE_TOKEN[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are processed throughout[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe codebase[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **HtmlHandler metadata handling**: Investigate all locations where document [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata is used to configure parsers or external tools, beyond just the [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexiftool_path field[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **CompositeParser and AutoDetectParser**: Examine how these parsers delegate to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExternalParser and whether other attack vectors exist[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Data URI scheme processing**: Review the complete `[0m[1;35mhandleDataURIScheme[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementation to understand what types of data URIs are processed and how they [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrigger embedded document extraction[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Configuration management**: Analyze how system properties versus document [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata are distinguished throughout Tika's configuration system[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Other ExternalParser invocations**: Search for all places where ExternalParser[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis instantiated or configured to ensure comprehensive protection[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Process execution patterns**: Review all uses of `[0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ProcessBuilder` across the codebase for similar vulnerabilities[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCommand Injection[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExecuting OS commands with attacker-controlled data can lead to remote code [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook[0m[1;39m([0m[39mOsC[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m408[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of the Issue[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe evaluation report reveals two distinct problems:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Compilation Error**: The previous patch attempt created a duplicate class [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclaration in HtmlHandler.java [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m: original declaration, line [0m[1;36m61[0m[39m: added [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduplicate[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, resulting in malformed code structure and an [0m[32m"reached end of file while[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mparsing"[0m[39m error at line [0m[1;36m646[0m[39m.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Underlying Security Vulnerability**: The original OS Command Injection [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability where document-controlled metadata [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`html_met[0m[1;92ma:e[0m[39mxiftool_path`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mused to configure external command execution through `[0m[1;35mExternalParser.setCommand[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Failed Patch Analysis[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch attempted to:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add necessary imports [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjava.nio.file.*, org.slf4j.*[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Block document metadata from specifying exiftool path[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Use system property `tika.exiftool.path` instead[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add validation in a new `[0m[1;35mconfigureExifTool[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, it failed due to:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Accidentally adding a second class declaration instead of modifying imports[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This created invalid Java syntax preventing compilation[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The unclosed code block prevented the file from being parsed correctly[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Comprehensive Fix Strategy[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Part [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Fix Compilation Error in HtmlHandler.java[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Issue**: Duplicate class declaration and syntax error[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Solution**: [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Add necessary imports cleanly without duplicating class declarations[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Add SLF4J logger import and instance declaration[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Ensure all code blocks are properly closed[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation**:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add imports after line [0m[1;36m22[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter existing imports[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  import java.nio.file.Files;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add logger imports after line [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter SAX imports[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add logger field after line [0m[1;36m55[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39minside the class, after the class declaration[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```java[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  private static final Logger LOG = [0m[1;35mLoggerFactory.getLogger[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlHandler.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **CRITICAL**: Do NOT add a second `public class HtmlHandler extends [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTextContentHandler` declaration[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep only the existing `class HtmlHandler extends TextContentHandler` at line [0m[1;36m55[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Part [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Fix Security Vulnerability - Remove Document-Controlled Configuration[0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexiftoolPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
